<h2><a name="isspace" id="isspace">isspace</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cctype&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> isspace<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> ch <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span></pre>
<p>

The isspace() function returns non-zero if its argument is some sort of space
(i.e. single space, tab, vertical tab, form feed, carriage return, or newline).
Otherwise, zero is returned.
</p>

